%h1 Typography

-# ========================================
-# Typographic scale

%h2 Scale

%p We use a typographic scale, most notably made famous by Robert Bringhurst. One off, large sizes to be used for hero, leader, or introduction sections are named <code>s-giga</code> and <code>s-mega</code>. General font sizes used across all headings and default text are named after the phonetic alphabet, <code>s-alpha</code> through <code>s-hotel</code>.

%p Our base <code>font-size</code> is <code>14</code> pixels and our base <code>line-height</code> is <code>24</code> pixels. Our <code>line-height</code>, and vertical spacing in general, should always a variable of <code>6</code> pixels. 

%p Any <code>font-size</code> of <code>12</code> pixels and under will use the Helvetica Neue typeface, as seen within <code>s-golf</code> and <code>s-hotel</code>.

%h5 Variables

%p For the <code>font-size</code>, and size alone, variables may be used. Example: <code>$s-alpha</code>, <code>$s-bravo</code>, <code>$s-charlie</code>, and etc.

%h5 Mixins &amp; Classes

%p For a <code>font-size</code> and <code>line-height</code> combination mixins and classes may be used. Mixin example: <code>+s-alpha</code>, <code>+s-bravo</code>, <code>+s-charlie</code>, and etc. Class example: <code>.s-alpha</code>, <code>.s-bravo</code>, <code>.s-charlie</code>, and etc.

